Dear Mike=2C=A0
>
> Does it not work to say that every internal category admits a weak
> equivalence functor to an internal category which is a stack?


Sure. This is so by Corollary 2.11 in Bunge-Pare. No problem with internal =
categories or internal weak equivalence functors of course. But how does on=
e internalize the notion of a stack? It comes down to parametrizing all epi=
morphisms in the topos itself.=A0

All the best=2CMarta


